  "text": "The complete chain from Deployment spec change to Pod creation in kubernetes/kubernetes v1.32.0 follows this flow:\n\n1. **Deployment Controller Reconciliation** (pkg/controller/deployment/deployment_controller.go:590)\n   - The `syncDeployment` method is the main entry point when a Deployment is created or modified\n   - It retrieves the Deployment object and its associated ReplicaSets, and determines which strategy to use (Recreate or RollingUpdate)\n   - For rolling updates, it calls `rolloutRolling` from the deployment sync module\n\n2. **Deployment Sync - Rolling Update Strategy** (pkg/controller/deployment/sync.go)\n   - The `sync` method coordinates scaling and handles the deployment reconciliation logic\n   - It retrieves or creates new ReplicaSets based on the Deployment's pod template\n   - It delegates actual Pod creation to the ReplicaSet controller by ensuring ReplicaSets have the correct replica count\n\n3. **ReplicaSet Controller Reconciliation** (pkg/controller/replicaset/replica_set.go:675)\n   - The `syncReplicaSet` method is invoked when a ReplicaSet is created or modified\n   - It calls `manageReplicas` (line 722) to reconcile the actual number of Pods with the desired replica count\n   - `manageReplicas` (line 569) determines how many Pods need to be created or deleted\n\n4. **Pod Creation via Controller** (pkg/controller/replicaset/replica_set.go:598)\n   - `manageReplicas` calls `rsc.podControl.CreatePods()` to create new Pods\n   - This uses the `RealPodControl` implementation defined in pkg/controller/controller_utils.go\n\n5. **Pod Control - API Client** (pkg/controller/controller_utils.go:578)\n   - `RealPodControl.createPods` prepares the Pod object and calls the Kubernetes API client\n   - At line 582, it calls `r.KubeClient.CoreV1().Pods(namespace).Create(ctx, pod, metav1.CreateOptions{})`\n   - This is the point where the Pod request is sent to the API server\n\n6. **Pod Storage in API Server** (pkg/registry/core/pod/storage/storage.go:72)\n   - The `NewStorage` function creates a `REST` struct that implements the RESTStorage interface\n   - It uses `registrypod.Strategy` (the podStrategy) for CreateStrategy at line 81\n   - The storage backend persists the Pod to etcd\n\n7. **Pod Strategy - Validation and Preparation** (pkg/registry/core/pod/strategy.go:66)\n   - `podStrategy` is the default logic for creating and updating Pods via REST API\n   - The `PrepareForCreate` method (line 86) initializes Pod status as Pending and applies any needed mutations\n   - Validation methods ensure the Pod specification is valid before storage\n\nThis chain demonstrates how a Deployment specification change triggers a cascade of controller reconciliations, ultimately resulting in Pod objects being created through the API server's storage layer."
